criteria.inclusion_criteria:
1. Female aged between 18-40 years old; 
2. Menorrhea or oligomenorrhea at least for 3-6 months;
3. FSH level above 25 IU/L (repeated twice >4 weeks apart);
4. Presence of  bilateral ovary;
5. No combined with male infertility;
6. Normal karyotype 46, XX;
7. Normal prolactin level within one year of study initiation;
8. Normal thyroid function as evidence by normal serum TSH levels;
9. Willing to attempt to get pregnant as part of the experimental protocol.Agree to report any pregnancy to the research staff immediately;
10.Willing and able to comply with study requirements.

criteria.exclusion_criteria:
1. History of gynecologic malignancy and pelvic surgery;
2. Contraindication to surgery or anesthesia;
3. Combined with major physical illnesses or  mental disorders, such as heart diseases, Type I or Type II diabetes mellitus, significant anemia that precludes performance of surgery;
